energy decrease during flares.\nThe discrepancy may partly be due to the pre-processing of photospheric vector\ndata, but more likely due to the non-forcefreeness in the lower chromosphere.\nWe conclude that the coronal field cannot be correctly calculated based on\nphotospheric data alone, but requires additional information on coronal loop\ngeometries.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Feb 2014 16:28:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-18"}
